Apple today released visionOS 2.4.1, a minor update to the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/visionos-2/">visionOS 2</a> operating system that came out in September. visionOS 2.4.1 <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/03/31/apple-releases-visionos-2-4/">comes two weeks</a> after the launch of visionOS 2.4.<br/>
<br/>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-955609" src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2024/06/visionOS-2-on-Apple-Vision-Pro-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" /><br/>
visionOS 2.4.1 can be downloaded on all Vision Pro headsets by navigating to the Settings app, selecting the General section, and choosing the Software Update option.<br/>
<br/>
To install an update, the Vision Pro headset needs to be removed, and there is a software progress bar available on the front EyeSight display.<br/>
<br/>
According to Apple's release notes, visionOS 2.4.1 includes bug fixes and security updates, and the software is recommended for all users.<br/>
<br/>
